        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-q">
            Should I get both arches or single arch?<svg
              class="chev"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              fill="none"
              stroke="currentColor"
              stroke-width="2"
            >
              <path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"></path>
            </svg>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-a">
            <div>
              <p>
                Most buyers choose both arches because upper-only veneers can
                look unnatural when you smile or talk — your lower teeth show,
                and a color mismatch between veneered upper teeth and natural
                lower teeth looks off. We recommend both unless your lower
                teeth are already in good shape. At $1,994 for both vs. $1,297
                for single, most people find the upgrade worth it.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-q">
            Am I a candidate for Revive Veneers?<svg
              class="chev"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              fill="none"
              stroke="currentColor"
              stroke-width="2"
            >
              <path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"></path>
            </svg>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-a">
            <div>
              <p>
                Most people are. Revive Veneers work well for anyone with
                healthy teeth and gums who wants to improve the appearance of
                stained, slightly gapped, or worn teeth. They aren't right for
                people with active gum disease, severe bite issues, multiple
                missing teeth at the end of the arch, or anyone currently
                wearing full dentures. Take our 30-second Smile Quiz above if
                you're unsure, it includes guidance on missing teeth and
                impression quality.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
